{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 04:36:07.076421", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nSummary of current network health\\n- Control plane: Healthy. All FRR EBGP sessions are established across leaves, spines, and the super-spine. Route tables on all routers contain the expected 10.pod.leaf.0/24 host routes and 172.16.x.x/31 interconnects. ECMP is present at the super-spine as expected.\\n- Data plane reachability: Healthy. Sampled end-to-end pings across many hosts show 0% packet loss and low baseline RTTs (typically 1–5 ms).\\n- Notable anomaly: Intermittent high latency observed specifically for traffic involving host pc_0_1, consistent with host-side traffic shaping.\\n\\nFindings and evidence\\n\\n1) End-to-end connectivity\\n- get_reachability: All tested host pairs reported 0% packet loss.\\n- Target pair (pc_0_0 <-> pc_0_1):\\n  - pc_0_0 -> pc_0_1: RTTs 2.7–46 ms, avg ~13.6 ms; single high spike (46 ms).\\n  - pc_0_1 -> pc_0_0: RTTs 2.2–48 ms, avg ~13.8 ms; single high spike (48 ms).\\n- Interpretation: Baseline RTT is normal (2–3 ms) with occasional large spikes when pc_0_1 is involved.\\n\\n2) Host configurations (pc_0_0 vs pc_0_1)\\n- pc_0_0:\\n  - NIC qdisc: fq_codel (normal default).\\n  - Default route: via 10.0.0.1.\\n- pc_0_1:\\n  - NIC qdisc: tbf traffic shaper on eth0.\\n  - tc -s qdisc show dev eth0:\\n    - qdisc tbf ... rate 30Kbit burst 64Kb lat 119s\\n  - Default route: via 10.0.1.1.\\n- Interpretation: pc_0_1 is explicitly rate-limited to 30 Kbit/s with a very large allowed queuing latency (119 s). This is highly atypical for a DC host NIC and will introduce queueing delay, jitter, and severe throughput capping for any traffic to/from pc_0_1. The RTT spikes seen in pings are consistent with queue buildup/drain on a TBF shaper.\\n\\n3) Routing control plane (FRR)\\n- leaf_router_0_0 and leaf_router_0_1: BGP summary shows 8 neighbors each, all Established; each neighbor advertising ~31 prefixes; RIB entries ~63.\\n- spine_router_0_1: 12 neighbors, all Established; PfxRcd 32 from super-spines and leaves; ECMP northbound; full routes installed.\\n- spine_router_0_0: 12 neighbors, all Established. Minor observation: PfxRcd shows 24 from superspine neighbors and a mix of 4/1 from some leaves; however, the routing table shows the expected set of host routes with northbound ECMP. No reachability issues detected as a result.\\n- super_spine_router_0: 32 neighbors, all Established; sending full set of prefixes to spines (PfxSnt 32). IP routing table shows expected ECMP to all 10.x/24 networks.\\n- Interpretation: The BGP fabric is up and converged. A small discrepancy in PfxRcd counters on spine_router_0_0 does not manifest as missing routes or reachability problems at this time.\\n\\nDetected anomaly and localization\\n- Anomaly: Host-side traffic shaping on pc_0_1 (eth0) using tc tbf at 30 Kbit/s with high latency.\\n- Localization: pc_0_1 (end host) NIC configuration.\\n- Impact: Any flows to/from pc_0_1 will suffer very low throughput, increased RTT, and jitter under load. This explains the sporadic high RTT samples between pc_0_0 and pc_0_1 despite an otherwise healthy fabric.\\n\\nRoot cause\\n- Misconfiguration on pc_0_1: A token bucket filter (tbf) is applied to eth0, rate-limiting to 30 Kbit/s and permitting large queueing delay (latency parameter set to 119 s). This host-level configuration is the direct cause of the observed intermittent high latency and will severely constrain throughput.\\n\\nAdditional minor observation\\n- BGP prefix counters on spine_router_0_0 show lower PfxRcd from super-spine neighbors compared to spine_router_0_1. Since the forwarding tables appear complete and data-plane tests show no loss, this is noted as a non-impacting inconsistency at present., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='9f7fac7e-a2de-48d2-b9d0-d3c185f227cf'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
